digraph build_remixos {
    graph [
        goal="Working RemixOS CRM platform with DB layer, HTTP server, 6 server-rendered views, REST API, Claude-powered command bar — all with tests passing, ruff clean, mypy clean",
        label="Build RemixOS CRM",
        retry_target="implement_db",
        default_max_retry=3,
        model_stylesheet="
            * { llm_model: claude-sonnet-4-5; llm_provider: anthropic; }
            .code { llm_model: claude-opus-4-6; llm_provider: anthropic; }
            .review { llm_model: claude-opus-4-6; reasoning_effort: high; }
        ",
        rankdir=TB
    ]

    // ==============================
    // START + RESUME SUPPORT
    // ==============================
    start [shape=Mdiamond, label="Start"]

    check_existing [shape=parallelogram,
        label="Check Existing Plans",
        tool_command="#!/bin/sh\nif [ -f docs/plans/plan.md ] && grep -q '^- \\[ \\]' docs/plans/plan.md 2>/dev/null; then\n  printf 'resume'\nelse\n  printf 'fresh'\nfi"]

    // ==============================
    // SCOPE ANALYSIS
    // ==============================
    scope_analysis [shape=box, class="review",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="scope_analysis",
        label="Scope Analysis",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Read the RemixOS spec and identify what is strictly needed for a working v1 CRM.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, stdlib http.server.ThreadingHTTPServer, SQLite 3, vanilla HTML/CSS/JS, Anthropic Claude API, pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Scope Rules — Apply YAGNI Ruthlessly
The spec describes 20 sections. For v1, we need the CORE CRM:
- Database layer (schema for all core tables, CRUD helpers, migration)
- HTTP server (ThreadingHTTPServer on port 8765, route dispatch, static serving)
- 6 views: Briefing, Pipeline, Clients, Offers, Tasks, Client Detail (all server-rendered HTML)
- Shared UI: sidebar navigation, CSS design tokens, client-side JavaScript
- REST API endpoints (CRUD for companies, deals, engagements, deliverables, people, offers)
- Command bar (Claude-powered NLP on every view)

CUT for v1 (integration work requiring external credentials):
- Nightly Sync (Google Drive contract detection)
- Calendar Integration (Google Calendar OAuth)
- LaunchAgents (depends on Nightly + Calendar)
- Chief of Staff Integration
- Staged Companies BD signal detection
- Skills System, Google Drive Integration, Agent Coordination (BBS)

## Deliverables
Write docs/plans/scope.md with IN/OUT sections listing every component and justification.

## Success Criteria
- docs/plans/scope.md exists with clear IN/OUT lists
- Commit: git add -A && git commit -m 'docs(scope): v1 scope analysis — core CRM only'
"]

    // ==============================
    // PLAN
    // ==============================
    plan [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="plan",
        label="Plan Architecture",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Plan the architecture for RemixOS v1 CRM. Read docs/plans/scope.md for what's in scope.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, stdlib http.server.ThreadingHTTPServer on port 8765, SQLite 3 (data/remix_crm.db), vanilla HTML/CSS/JS (server-rendered, no framework), Anthropic Claude API (for command bar), pytest, ruff, mypy. Use uv for package management.

## Deliverables
Write docs/plans/plan.md with:
1. Directory structure: src/remixos/ with modules for db.py, server.py, views/, api.py, command_bar.py, styles.py, scripts.py
2. Implementation order with task checkboxes in format: - [ ] task-N: description
3. Dependency graph showing build order
4. Test strategy per module (what to test, how to mock)

## Success Criteria
- docs/plans/plan.md exists with task checkboxes
- No handwaving — every task must be specific and actionable
- Commit: git add -A && git commit -m 'docs(plan): architecture plan for RemixOS v1'
"]

    // ==============================
    // VALIDATE PLAN FORMAT
    // ==============================
    validate_plan [shape=parallelogram,
        label="Validate Plan Format",
        tool_command="#!/bin/sh\nset -eu\nPLAN='docs/plans/plan.md'\nif [ ! -s \"$PLAN\" ]; then printf 'fail_no_plan'; exit 0; fi\ncount=$(grep -c '^- \\[ \\] task-[0-9]\\+:' \"$PLAN\" || true)\nif [ \"$count\" -eq 0 ]; then printf 'fail_no_checkboxes'; exit 0; fi\nhandwaves=$(grep -ciE '(write a complete implementation|add appropriate|add validation logic|add error handling logic|add the logic)' \"$PLAN\" || true)\nif [ \"$handwaves\" -gt 0 ]; then printf 'fail_handwaves'; exit 0; fi\nprintf 'format_ok'"]

    // ==============================
    // SETUP
    // ==============================
    setup [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="setup",
        label="Setup Project",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Initialize the RemixOS Python project with all tooling and pre-commit hooks.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, uv for package management. Dependencies: anthropic. Dev deps: pytest, pytest-cov, ruff, mypy, pre-commit.

## Process
1. Run: uv init (if no pyproject.toml exists)
2. Run: uv add anthropic
3. Run: uv add --dev pytest pytest-cov ruff mypy pre-commit
4. Configure ruff in pyproject.toml: line-length=120, target-version='py312'
5. Configure mypy in pyproject.toml: strict mode, python_version='3.12'
6. Create .pre-commit-config.yaml with hooks for ruff check, ruff format, mypy
7. Run: uv run pre-commit install
8. Run: uv run pre-commit run --all-files
9. Create directory structure:
   - src/remixos/ (with __init__.py)
   - src/remixos/views/ (with __init__.py)
   - tests/
   - data/
   - templates/
   - static/css/
   - static/js/
   - docs/
10. Create .gitignore with: __pycache__, .mypy_cache, .ruff_cache, .pytest_cache, data/*.db, .venv, *.pyc
11. Commit: git add -A && git commit -m 'chore(setup): initialize project with deps and pre-commit hooks'

## Success Criteria
- pyproject.toml exists with all deps
- Pre-commit hooks installed and passing
- Directory structure created
- ruff and mypy configured
"]

    // ==============================
    // FOUNDATION: DB LAYER
    // ==============================
    implement_db [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="implement_db",
        label="Implement DB Layer",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Write failing tests FIRST, then implement the SQLite database layer.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, SQLite 3 (database file: data/remix_crm.db), pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Schema (core tables)
Implement these tables with proper types, constraints, and foreign keys:
- companies (id TEXT PK, name TEXT NOT NULL, domain, industry, description, city, state, country, drive_folder_path, created_at)
- people (id TEXT PK, company_id FK, first_name, last_name, name, email, phone, job_title, created_at)
- offers (id TEXT PK slug, name TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE, creates_engagement BOOLEAN DEFAULT 1, description, created_at)
- deals (id TEXT PK, name TEXT NOT NULL, company_id FK, offer_id FK, value REAL, stage TEXT NOT NULL, owner TEXT CHECK IN justin/jason, target_close_date, last_contact_date, notes, next_steps_text, sort_order INTEGER, created_at, closed_at)
- engagements (id TEXT PK, deal_id FK, company_id FK, offer_id FK, name, start_date, end_date, status TEXT CHECK IN active/completed/paused/cancelled DEFAULT active, owner, created_at)
- deliverables (id TEXT PK, engagement_id FK, name TEXT NOT NULL, description, due_date, owner, status TEXT CHECK IN not_started/in_progress/complete DEFAULT not_started, deliverable_type TEXT CHECK IN meeting/artifact, created_at)
- staged_engagements (id TEXT PK, company_id FK, offer_id FK, name, start_date, end_date, contract_value REAL, source_file_path, proposed_deliverables TEXT JSON, status TEXT DEFAULT pending, created_at)
- contractors (id TEXT PK, name TEXT NOT NULL, email, specialty, hourly_rate REAL, created_at)

## Modules to Implement
1. src/remixos/db.py:
   - get_connection() -> sqlite3.Connection (to data/remix_crm.db)
   - db_connection() context manager
   - migrate_database() — creates all tables if not exist, adds indexes
   - CRUD helpers: get_companies(), get_company(id), create_company(**kwargs), update_company(id, **kwargs)
   - Same pattern for: deals, engagements, deliverables, people, offers, staged_engagements
   - Seed offers with standard set (kickstart, aiba, subscription, design_sprints, etc.)

## Process
1. Write failing tests in tests/test_db.py covering: schema creation, CRUD for each entity, foreign key constraints, seed data
2. Run: uv run pytest tests/test_db.py -v — confirm tests FAIL
3. Implement src/remixos/db.py minimally to pass tests
4. Run: uv run ruff check . --fix && uv run ruff format .
5. Run: uv run mypy src/
6. Fix all issues

## Success Criteria
- All DB tests pass
- ruff and mypy clean
- Schema matches spec
- CRUD helpers work for all entities
"]

    verify_db [shape=diamond,
        label="DB Tests Pass?",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.
Run:
1. uv run pytest tests/test_db.py -v --tb=short
2. uv run ruff check .
3. uv run mypy src/
If ALL pass: outcome=success
If ANY fail: outcome=fail"]

    commit_db [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="implement_db",
        label="Commit DB",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.
Review changes with git diff. Stage all relevant files.
git add -A && git commit -m 'feat(db): implement SQLite schema with CRUD helpers and seed data'
Do NOT commit data/*.db files.
Verify: git log --oneline -1"]

    // ==============================
    // FOUNDATION: HTTP SERVER
