    implement_server [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="implement_server",
        label="Implement HTTP Server",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Write failing tests FIRST, then implement the HTTP server with route dispatch.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, stdlib http.server.ThreadingHTTPServer on port 8765, pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Modules to Implement
1. src/remixos/server.py:
   - RemixOSHandler(BaseHTTPRequestHandler) with do_GET() and do_POST()
   - Route dispatch: map URL paths to handler functions
   - Static file serving for /static/* paths
   - JSON response helpers: send_json(data, status=200), send_error(message, status)
   - HTML response helper: send_html(content)
   - Query string parsing for page parameters (week_offset, etc.)
   - main() function: migrate_database(), start ThreadingHTTPServer on port 8765
   - REMIXOS_NO_BROWSER env var support

2. GET routes (return placeholder HTML for now — views come later):
   / -> briefing, /clients -> clients, /clients/{id} -> client detail,
   /pipeline -> pipeline, /offers -> offers, /tasks -> tasks

3. POST routes (wire up to DB CRUD):
   /api/command -> placeholder, /api/deal/{id}/update, /api/deal/create,
   /api/deliverable/{id}/update, /api/staged/{id}/activate, /api/staged/{id}/reject

## Process
1. Write failing tests in tests/test_server.py: route dispatch, static serving, JSON/HTML responses, API endpoints
2. Run: uv run pytest tests/test_server.py -v — confirm FAIL
3. Implement server.py
4. Run: uv run ruff check . --fix && uv run ruff format .
5. Run: uv run mypy src/

## Success Criteria
- Server starts on port 8765
- All routes dispatch correctly
- API endpoints return proper JSON
- Tests pass, ruff clean, mypy clean
"]

