## Task
Write failing tests FIRST, then implement the shared CSS design tokens and client-side JavaScript.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, vanilla CSS/JS (generated as Python strings, server-rendered inline), pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Modules to Implement
1. src/remixos/styles.py — get_base_styles() returns CSS string:
   - Design tokens: colors (Remix blue #2563eb, grays, status colors), typography (system font stack), spacing scale
   - Layout: sidebar (collapsible, 260px expanded / 60px collapsed), main content area
   - Component styles: cards, tables, badges, buttons, modals, forms
   - Pipeline kanban columns, Gantt chart rows, briefing 3-column layout
   - Responsive breakpoints
   - Command bar fixed at bottom

2. src/remixos/scripts.py — get_base_scripts() returns JS string:
   - Sidebar toggle (localStorage.sidebarCollapsed persistence)
   - Command bar: input handling, POST to /api/command, response display, conversation history
   - Modal open/close logic
   - Fetch helpers for API calls (POST JSON, handle errors)
   - Form submission handlers

3. src/remixos/views/sidebar.py — get_sidebar_html(active_view) returns sidebar HTML:
   - Remix Partners logo (SVG)
   - Navigation links: Briefing(/), Pipeline(/pipeline), Clients(/clients), Tasks(/tasks), Offers(/offers)
   - Active state highlighting
   - Collapse toggle button
   - Shutdown button

## Process
1. Write tests in tests/test_styles.py: verify CSS contains required tokens, JS contains required functions, sidebar renders with correct active state
2. Run: uv run pytest tests/test_styles.py -v — confirm FAIL
3. Implement modules
4. Run: uv run ruff check . --fix && uv run ruff format .
5. Run: uv run mypy src/

## Success Criteria
- CSS has all design tokens and component styles
- JS has sidebar toggle, command bar, modal, and fetch helpers
- Sidebar renders with correct navigation and active state
- Tests pass, ruff clean, mypy clean
"]

