## Task
Write failing tests FIRST, then implement the Claude-powered natural language command bar.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, Anthropic Claude API (anthropic SDK), REST API layer (src/remixos/api.py), pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Module: src/remixos/command_bar.py
Function: process_command(text: str, view_context: dict) -> dict

The command bar is the primary input mechanism. Users type natural language like:
- 'move Acme to Won' -> update deal stage
- 'mark the kickoff complete' -> update deliverable status
- 'add a deal for Globex, qualifying, 50k' -> create deal
- 'delete it' -> understands from conversation context

Implementation:
1. Build a system prompt that describes available actions and current view context
2. Send user text + conversation history to Claude API
3. Claude returns structured tool calls (update_deal, create_deal, update_deliverable, etc.)
4. Execute the tool calls via api.py functions
5. Return result summary to display in command bar

Conversation memory: maintain list of recent messages (in-memory per request, passed from client JS).

Wire into server: update api.py process_command() to call command_bar.process_command().

## Process
1. Write tests in tests/test_command_bar.py: test command parsing, tool call execution, error handling
2. Mock the Anthropic API in tests (use unittest.mock to patch anthropic client)
3. Confirm FAIL, implement, run ruff + mypy

## Success Criteria
- Command bar correctly interprets natural language commands
- Tool calls map to API functions
- Conversation context maintained
- Tests pass with mocked Claude API
- ruff + mypy clean
"]

    verify_command_bar [shape=diamond,
        label="Command Bar Tests Pass?",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.
Run:
1. uv run pytest tests/test_command_bar.py -v --tb=short
2. uv run ruff check .
3. uv run mypy src/
If ALL pass: outcome=success
If ANY fail: outcome=fail"]

    commit_command_bar [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="implement_command_bar",
        label="Commit Command Bar",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.
git add -A && git commit -m 'feat(cmdbar): implement Claude-powered NLP command bar with tool calling'
Verify: git log --oneline -1"]

    // ==============================
    // BUDGET TRACKING
    // ==============================
    check_budget [shape=parallelogram,
        label="Check Retry Budget",
        tool_command="#!/bin/sh\nset -eu\nmkdir -p .tracker\nCOUNTER='.tracker/e2e_count'\ncount=0\n[ -f \"$COUNTER\" ] && count=$(cat \"$COUNTER\")\ncount=$((count + 1))\nprintf '%s' \"$count\" > \"$COUNTER\"\nif [ \"$count\" -gt 5 ]; then\n  printf 'budget_exhausted'\nelse\n  printf 'budget_ok'\nfi"]

    // ==============================
    // E2E TESTS
    // ==============================
    e2e_tests [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="e2e_tests",
        label="E2E Tests",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Write and run end-to-end tests that exercise the full stack.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, pytest, all RemixOS modules, SQLite (test database).

## Tests to Write (tests/test_e2e.py)
1. Server startup: start server, verify it responds on port 8765
2. View rendering: GET each route (/,/pipeline,/clients,/offers,/tasks), verify HTML contains expected elements
3. API CRUD flow: POST create deal -> GET pipeline (verify deal appears) -> POST update deal stage -> verify stage changed
4. Staged engagement flow: create staged engagement in DB -> POST activate -> verify engagement + deliverables created
5. Sidebar navigation: verify all views have sidebar with correct active state
6. CSS/JS inclusion: verify views include design tokens and required JS functions

## Process
1. Write tests using a test client that starts the server in a thread with a test DB
2. Run: uv run pytest tests/test_e2e.py -v --tb=long
3. Run: uv run ruff check . && uv run mypy src/
4. Fix all failures

## Success Criteria
- Full user flows work end-to-end
- All 6 views render correctly with data from DB
- API endpoints create/update/delete correctly
- Tests pass, ruff clean, mypy clean
"]

    // ==============================
    // LANGUAGE-AWARE BUILD VALIDATION
    // ==============================
    validate_build [shape=parallelogram,
        label="Validate Full Build",
        tool_command="set -eu\nif [ -f pyproject.toml ]; then\n  uv run pytest -v 2>&1 || exit 1\n  uv run ruff check . 2>&1 || exit 1\n  printf 'validation-pass'\nelse\n  printf 'validation-unknown'\nfi"]

    commit_final [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="e2e_tests",
        label="Commit Final",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.
git add -A && git commit -m 'test(e2e): add end-to-end tests for full RemixOS stack'
Verify: git log --oneline -1"]

    // ==============================
    // FINAL REVIEW (IRON LAW)
    // ==============================
    review [shape=box, class="review",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="e2e_tests",
        label="Final Review",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## IRON LAW: NO COMPLETION CLAIMS WITHOUT FRESH VERIFICATION
Run commands. Read output. Check exit codes. THEN make claims.

## Context (MANDATORY — do this FIRST)
1. Get the full diff: git log --oneline --all
2. Read every changed source file in src/remixos/
3. Run the test suite: uv run pytest -v --tb=short
4. Run linting: uv run ruff check . && uv run mypy src/
DO NOT trust the implementer's claims. Verify independently.

## Checklist
- [ ] DB layer: schema matches spec (all core tables, correct types, FKs, indexes)
- [ ] Server: routes dispatch correctly, static serving works
- [ ] All 6 views render with correct data and sidebar
- [ ] CSS has design tokens, JS has command bar + sidebar toggle
- [ ] API endpoints handle CRUD for deals, deliverables, staged engagements
- [ ] Command bar processes natural language via Claude API
- [ ] All tests pass (unit, integration, e2e)
- [ ] ruff clean, mypy clean
- [ ] Pre-commit hooks working
- [ ] No hardcoded paths, no secrets in code

If all checks pass: outcome=success
If any issues found: outcome=fail
"]

    // ==============================
    // GRADUATED ESCALATION
    // ==============================
    debug_investigate [shape=box, class="code",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="debug_investigate",
        label="Debug Investigation",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
The build or tests failed. Investigate the root cause systematically.

## Tech Stack
Python 3.12, pytest, ruff, mypy.

## Process
1. Read the FULL test output — don't skim
2. Identify which specific test(s) failed and why
3. Read the relevant source files
4. Check for common issues: import errors, missing DB migrations, route mismatches, template rendering bugs
5. Apply targeted fix — do NOT rewrite working code
6. Run: uv run pytest -v --tb=long
7. Run: uv run ruff check . && uv run mypy src/

If fixed: outcome=success
If cannot fix after thorough investigation: outcome=fail
"]

    replan_task [shape=box, class="review",
        goal_gate=true, retry_target="replan_task",
        label="Replan Approach",
        prompt="You are working in `run.working_dir`.

## Task
Debug investigation failed to fix the issue. Step back and replan.

## Process
1. Read all test failures and error logs
2. Identify if the approach is fundamentally wrong (architecture issue vs bug)
3. If architecture issue: revise the module structure in docs/plans/plan.md
4. If integration issue: identify which components aren't wiring together correctly
5. Apply the revised approach
6. Run: uv run pytest -v

If replanned and fixed: outcome=success
If still stuck: outcome=fail
"]

    // ==============================
    // DONE
    // ==============================
    done [shape=Msquare, label="Done"]

    // ==============================
    // EDGES
    // ==============================

    // Start -> Resume check
    start -> check_existing;
    check_existing -> scope_analysis [label="fresh start", condition="context.tool_stdout=fresh"];
    check_existing -> e2e_tests [label="resume", condition="context.tool_stdout=resume", weight=2];

    // Scope -> Plan -> Validate -> Setup
    scope_analysis -> plan;
    plan -> validate_plan;
    validate_plan -> setup [label="format ok", condition="context.tool_stdout=format_ok", weight=2];
    validate_plan -> plan [label="fix plan", condition="context.tool_stdout!=format_ok"];

    // Foundation: DB -> Server (sequential — server depends on DB)
    setup -> implement_db;
    implement_db -> verify_db;
    verify_db -> commit_db [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_db -> implement_db [label="fix", condition="outcome=fail"];

    commit_db -> implement_server;
    implement_server -> verify_server;
    verify_server -> commit_server [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_server -> implement_server [label="fix", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // Foundation verification
    commit_server -> verify_foundation;
    verify_foundation -> implement_styles [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_foundation -> implement_db [label="fix foundation", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // Styles (must come before views — views depend on get_base_styles/get_sidebar_html)
    implement_styles -> verify_styles;
    verify_styles -> commit_styles [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_styles -> implement_styles [label="fix", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // Fan-out: 6 views in parallel (all depend on DB + Server + Styles, not on each other)
    commit_styles -> fan_out_views;
    fan_out_views -> implement_briefing;
    fan_out_views -> implement_pipeline;
    fan_out_views -> implement_clients;
    fan_out_views -> implement_offers;
    fan_out_views -> implement_tasks;
    fan_out_views -> implement_client_detail;

    // Fan-in: all views complete
    implement_briefing -> fan_in_views;
    implement_pipeline -> fan_in_views;
    implement_clients -> fan_in_views;
    implement_offers -> fan_in_views;
    implement_tasks -> fan_in_views;
    implement_client_detail -> fan_in_views;

    fan_in_views -> verify_views;
    verify_views -> commit_views [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_views -> implement_briefing [label="fix views", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // API (parallel with views — both depend on DB + Server, not on each other)
    commit_styles -> implement_api;
    implement_api -> verify_api;
    verify_api -> commit_api [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_api -> implement_api [label="fix", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // Join: Views + API -> Command Bar
    commit_views -> join_command_bar;
    commit_api -> join_command_bar;
    join_command_bar -> implement_command_bar;

    implement_command_bar -> verify_command_bar;
    verify_command_bar -> commit_command_bar [label="pass", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    verify_command_bar -> implement_command_bar [label="fix", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // E2E with budget tracking
    commit_command_bar -> check_budget;
    check_budget -> e2e_tests [label="budget ok", condition="context.tool_stdout=budget_ok", weight=2];
    check_budget -> replan_task [label="budget exhausted", condition="context.tool_stdout=budget_exhausted"];

    // E2E -> Validate -> Review
    e2e_tests -> validate_build;
    validate_build -> commit_final [label="pass", condition="context.tool_stdout=validation-pass", weight=2];
    validate_build -> debug_investigate [label="fail", condition="context.tool_stdout!=validation-pass"];

    commit_final -> review;
    review -> done [label="all good", condition="outcome=success", weight=2];
    review -> debug_investigate [label="issues found", condition="outcome=fail"];

    // Graduated escalation
    debug_investigate -> e2e_tests [label="fixed", condition="outcome=success"];
    debug_investigate -> replan_task [label="can't fix", condition="outcome=fail"];
    replan_task -> e2e_tests [label="replanned", condition="outcome=success"];
    replan_task -> done [label="stuck — ship what works", condition="outcome=fail"];
}
